e I will be hidden; I will be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth, and whoever finds me will kill me.”"}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"\"Behold, You have driven me this day from the face of the ground; and from Your face I will be hidden, and I will be a vagrant and a wanderer on the earth, and whoever finds me will kill me.\""}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"Surely You have driven me out this day from the face of the ground; I shall be hidden from Your face; I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond on the earth, and it will happen "}, {:version=>" anyone who finds me will kill me.”", :text=>"King James Bible"}, {:version=>"Behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the earth; and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it shall come to pass, ", :text=>" every one that findeth me shall slay me."}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"Since you are banishing me today from the face of the earth, and I must hide from your presence and become a restless wanderer on the earth, whoever finds me will kill me.\""}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"\"You're making me leave my home and live far from you. I will have to wander about without a home, and just anyone could kill me.\" "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"You are driving me off the land and away from your presence. I will be a homeless wanderer on the earth, and anyone who finds me will kill me.\" "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"Since You are banishing me today from the soil, and I must hide myself from Your presence and become a restless wanderer on the earth, whoever finds me will kill me.\" "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"\"You're driving me from the soil today. I'll be hidden from you, and I'll wander throughout the earth as a fugitive. In the future, whoever finds me will kill me.\""}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"Look! You are driving me off the land today, and I must hide from your presence. I will be a homeless wanderer on the earth; whoever finds me will kill me.\""}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"Look, you have driven me out this day from the surface of the ground. I will be hidden from your face, and I will be a fugitive and a wanderer in the earth. It will happen that whoever finds me will kill me.\""}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"You have forced me off this land today. I have to hide from you and become a fugitive, a wanderer on the earth. Now anyone who finds me will kill me!\""}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"Behold, Thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the land; and from Thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer in the earth; and it will come to pass, that whosoever findeth me will slay me.'"}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"“Behold, Thou hast driven me this day from the face of the ground; and from Thy face I shall be hidden, and I shall be a vagrant and a wanderer on the earth, and it will come about that whoever finds me will kill me.”"}, {:version=>"King James 2000 Bible", :text=>"Behold, you have driven me out this day from the face of the earth; and from your face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer in the earth; and it shall come to pass, that anyone that finds me shall slay me."}, {:version=>"American King James Version", :text=>"Behold, you have driven me out this day from the face of the earth; and from your face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it shall come to pass, that every one that finds me shall slay me."}, {:version=>"American Standard Version", :text=>"Behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the ground; and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer in the earth; and it will come to pass, that whosoever findeth me will slay me."}, {:version=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation", :text=>"If thou castest me out this day from the face of the earth, and I shall be hidden from thy presence, and I shall be groaning and trembling upon the earth, then it will be that any one that finds me shall slay me."}, {:version=>"Douay-Rheims Bible", :text=>"Behold thou dost cast me out this day from the face of the earth, and I shall be hidden from thy face, and I shall be a vagabond and a fugitive on the earth: everyone, therefore, that findeth me, shall kill me. "}, {:version=>"Darby Bible Translation", :text=>"Behold, thou hast driven me this day from the face of the ground, and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a wanderer and fugitive on the earth; and it will come to pass, [that] every one who finds me will slay me."}, {:version=>"English Revised Version", :text=>"Behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the ground; and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer in the earth; and it shall come to pass, that whosoever findeth me shall slay me."}, {:version=>"Webster's Bible Translation", :text=>"Behold, thou hast driven me this day from the face of the earth; and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it will come to pass, that every one that findeth me will slay me."}, {:version=>"World English Bible", :text=>"Behold, you have driven me out this day from the surface of the ground. I will be hidden from your face, and I will be a fugitive and a wanderer in the earth. It will happen that whoever finds me will kill me.\""}, {:version=>"Young's Literal Translation", :text=>" lo, Thou hast driven me to-day from off the face of the ground, and from Thy face I am hid; and I have been a wanderer, even a trembling one, in the earth, and it hath been -- every one finding me doth slay me.'"}]}